  "title": "Research Fellow (Mathematics)",
  "description": "<p>Interested applicants are invited to apply directly at the <a href=\"https://careers.nus.edu.sg/job/Research-Fellow-%28Mathematics%29/31504-en_GB/?st=C18F0A1A9F71539D1D1980E9047B816B023431C5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>NUS\nCareer Portal</strong></a></p><p>Your application will be processed only if you apply\nvia <a href=\"https://careers.nus.edu.sg/job/Research-Fellow-%28Mathematics%29/31504-en_GB/?st=C18F0A1A9F71539D1D1980E9047B816B023431C5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>NUS\nCareer Portal</strong></a></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.<br /></p><h2><strong>Job Description</strong></h2><p>The successful candidate will work with Dr. Wei Daren in intersection of Lie groups, geometry and dynamical systems, focusing on rigidity of group actions and the Zimmer program.</p><p><br />The main responsibilities of the position include: <br />(i) To perform excellent research with Dr. Wei Daren and his team of students and research fellows, leading to publications in top venues on geometry and dynamics  <br />(ii) To teach one class in the Mathematics department per semester.</p><p><br /><strong>Qualifications / Discipline:</strong><br />•    Ph.D. in Mathematics</p><p><br /><strong>Skills:  </strong><br />•    Mathematics with a focus on geometry and dynamical systems</p><p><br /><strong>Experience:  </strong><br />•    4 years of doing research on intersection of Lie groups, geometry, and dynamical systems, with a particular focus on Lie group actions on manifolds and their rigidity phenomena.</p>",
